orego.mcts

Class McRunnable

  • java.lang.Object
    • orego.mcts.McRunnable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LgrfMcRunnable, WLSMcRunnable

    public class McRunnable
extends Object
implements Runnable
    Players use this class to perform multiple Monte Carlo runs in different threads.

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int MERCY_THRESHOLD
      If one player's number of stones on the board exceeds the opponent's by this much, the playout is considered a win for that player.

      • performMcRun

        public void performMcRun()
        Performs a single Monte Carlo run and incorporates it into player's search tree. The player should generate moves to the frontier of the known tree, add a 'node', and then return. We will handle performing the actual playout in the aptly named playout.

      • playout

        public int playout()
        Plays moves to the end of the game and returns the winner: BLACK, WHITE, or (in rare event where the playout is canceled because it hits the maximum number of moves) VACANT.
